{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a67417cc3fb48d66757", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba5"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "615d92ebde3d91842a5cf7ec", "title": "JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "approximateTimeRequired": 150, "question": {"text": "A hydrogen atom, initially in the ground state is excited by absorbing a photon of wavelength $980 \u00c3\u2026$. The radius of the atom in the excited state, in terms of Bohr radius $a_{0}$, will be:", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "Ulbx6", "text": "$25 \\mathrm{a}_{0}$", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "wLwpi", "text": "$9 a_{0}$", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "rlChF", "text": "$16 \\mathrm{a}_{0}$", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "FeF3Y", "text": "None of the above", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "Energy of photon $=\\frac{\\mathrm{hc}}{\\lambda}=\\frac{12500}{980}=12.75 \\mathrm{eV}$\r\n\r\nEnergy of electron in $\\mathrm{n}^{\\text {th }}$ orbit is given by\r\n\r\n$\\mathrm{En}=\\frac{-13.6}{\\mathrm{n}^{2}} \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{E}_{\\mathrm{n}}-\\mathrm{E}_{1}=-13.6\\left[\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{n}^{2}} \\frac{-1}{1^{2}}\\right]$\r\n\r\n$\\Rightarrow 12.75=13.6\\left[\\frac{1}{1^{2}} \\frac{-1}{\\mathrm{n}^{2}}\\right] \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{n}=4$\r\n\r\n$\\therefore$ Electron will excite to $\\mathrm{n}=4$ We know that ' $R^{\\prime} \\propto n^{2}$\r\n\r\n$\\therefore$ Radius of atom will be $16 \\mathrm{a}_{0}$", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "questionLabels": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ08413100", "category": null, "source": "EM", "bucket": "Must Do Ques (JEE Main) - Any Difficulty", "numeri